7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Claude and Microsoft Copilot share a solid foundation of core features including Web Search, File Upload, Code Execution, Image Generation. Where Claude pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Microsoft Copilot uniquely offers Voice Input and Plugins, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Claude holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Microsoft Copilot scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Claude and Microsoft Copilot offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Claude's free tier and Microsoft Copilot's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
